<!-- If this is a letter or similar with an opener (with content such as dateline and/or salute) add it. For example: -->          	
<opener>
<lb/><space extent="10" unit="words"/><add place="inspace" rend="gray small" hand="#U1">MS 8/3</add><!-- Change line info as appropriate -->
<lb/><dateline><space extent="4" unit="words"/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/><placeName><settlement type="village">Kolobeng</settlement></placeName> <date when="1849-10-15">15 October 1849<!-- Change line info as appropriate --><!-- Begin each line with <lb/> as here --></date></dateline>
<lb/>    
<lb/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/><salute>My very dear Friends</salute><!-- Change line info as appropriate -->
</opener>

<lb/><p><space extent="4" unit="words"/>I believe I told you in my 
<lb/>last that I intended to visit a reported Lake in
<lb/>the regions beyond us. I am happy to say
<lb/>that after a <measure>1200 miles</measure> trip I have been
<lb/>permitted to return in safety having seen
<lb/>the Lake and a people speaking a different
<lb/>language from the <term type="tribe"><choice><orig>Bechuana</orig><reg>Batswana</reg></choice></term>- After
<lb/>travelling <measure>300 miles</measure> we struck the beautiful 
<lb/>river <placeName><geogName type="river">Zouga</geogName></placeName> and then by winding along
<lb/>its banks about <measure>300 more</measure> to the westward
<lb/>we came to the <placeName><geogName type="lake">Lake Ngami</geogName></placeName>. The river
<lb/>is very beautiful indeed - it is subject
<lb/>to a periodical rise &amp; fall &amp; probably derives
<lb/>its water from melting snow. It was
<lb/>rising when <add place="above">we</add> were there &amp; was notwithstanding
<lb/>perfectly pure - from <measure>50 yards wide</measure> <gap extent="1" unit="words"/><supplied cert="low">where</supplied>
<lb/>we struck it widened as we ascended till
<lb/>it was more than a <measure><app><rdg>160</rdg><rdg>100</rdg></app> yards</measure> of deep
<lb/>water between a broad belt of <term type="plant">reed</term> growing
<lb/>with shallower parts<space extent="1" unit="chars"/>. <space extent="3" unit="chars"/>great shoals
<lb/>o<supplied cert="high">f</supplied> <term type="animal_foodstuff">fish</term> come down with the water - 	
	
            	
	<pb facs="liv_000683_0002" n="0002"/>
<lb/>and the <term type="tribe">Bakoba</term> catch them with nets - they
<lb/>are darker in complexion than <term type="tribe"><choice><orig>Bechuana</orig><reg>Batswana</reg></choice></term>
<lb/>and paddle along the Lake &amp; rivers <choice><sic>ajasent</sic><corr>adjacent</corr></choice> in
<lb/>canoes - I often <unclear><w>sai<subst><del>d</del><add place="over-text">led</add></subst></w></unclear> along in them &amp; visted 
<lb/>their villages, as the wagon went along the
<lb/>bank - They seemed to understand the message	
<lb/>of mercy better than any people I ever spoke	
<lb/>to for the first time - We all admired the frankness
<lb/>of their manners - We reached the <term type="tribe"><choice><orig>Bataoana</orig><reg>Batawana</reg></choice></term> on
<lb/><date when="1849-08-01">the first of August</date> &amp; rode <measure>6 miles</measure> beyond to
<lb/>the broadest part of the Lake - It presented a
<lb/>horizon of water to the South South West - so we
<lb/>could not tell its size <space extent="3" unit="chars"/> it may be <measure>70 miles</measure>
<lb/>long for a native takes three days to walk
<lb/>around to the narrow part at the <choice><abbr>Norwest</abbr><expan>North West</expan></choice>	
<lb/>the banks of the <placeName><geogName type="river">Tonga</geogName></placeName> however with the
<lb/><placeName><geogName type="river">Tarnunakle</geogName></placeName> flowing into it arrested nearly
<lb/>all my thoughts - they are extremely beautiful
<lb/>and seem like a navigable highway into
<lb/>a large section of country - gigantic trees
<lb/>line their banks - three of these are new
<lb/>&amp; fruit-bearing - one I saw on the opposite
<lb/>bank of the <placeName><geogName type="river"><choice><abbr>T.</abbr><expan>Tonga</expan></choice></geogName></placeName>had fruit more than <measure>a foot
<lb/>long &amp; 3 inches in diameter</measure> hanging from its

	<pb facs="liv_000683_0003" n="0003"/>
<lb/>branches - the tribes we visted were the <term type="tribe"><choice><orig>Bakurutse</orig><reg>Bahurutse</reg></choice></term>
<lb/><term type="tribe">Battelle</term> - <term type="tribe"><choice><orig>Bataoana</orig><reg>Batawana</reg></choice></term> &amp; <term type="tribe">Bakoba</term> - - I wished to visit
<lb/>a tribe <measure>200 miles</measure> beyond but the <term type="tribe"><choice><orig>Bataoana</orig><reg>Batawana</reg></choice></term>
<lb/><term type="occupation">chief</term> kept all the canoes at the ford out of our
<lb/>sight - as it was - I have been absent from
<lb/>wife &amp; family for 4 months and 10 days.
<lb/>The gentlemen who came from <placeName><country>England</country></placeName>
<lb/>to accompany me are passing homewards
<lb/>I have not time to write you at length
<lb/>but give you a few lines rather than
<lb/>none at <choice><sic>at</sic><corr/></choice> all - the <choice><abbr>Noreast</abbr><expan>North East</expan></choice> Extremity
<lb/>of the Lake is in <measure>20° 20' <choice><abbr>S.</abbr><expan>South</expan></choice></measure> the <choice><abbr>long.</abbr><expan>longitude</expan></choice>
<lb/>may be 24° <choice><abbr>E.</abbr><expan>East</expan></choice>. <space extent="5" unit="chars"/> I think I told you in <choice><sic>in</sic><corr/></choice>
<lb/>my last that we had another son. <persName>M<hi rend="sup">rs.</hi> <choice><abbr>L.</abbr><expan>Livingstone</expan></choice></persName>
<lb/>united with me in very kind salutations
<lb/>to you and your family - May you
<lb/>enjoy every needed blessing -</p>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="4" unit="words"/>affectionately yours</p><!-- Change as appropriate -->
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="6" unit="words"/><persName><choice><abbr>D</abbr><expan>David</expan></choice> Livingstone</persName></p><!-- Change as appropriate --> 
<lb/>
<lb/><p rend="no-indent"><space extent="2" unit="chars"/>We expect <persName>M<hi rend="sup">r</hi> Freeman</persName> soon</p>

      
	<pb facs="liv_000683_0004" n="0004"/>

<lb/><ab><space extent="5" unit="words"/><add rend="gray" hand="#U2"><placeName><geogName type="river">River Za<gap extent="5" unit="chars"/></geogName></placeName></add></ab>
	
	<cb rend="left vertical"/>
	<ab><address>
<addrLine><del type="cancelled">Care of <unclear cert="low">Rio W. Blaly's</unclear> <placeName><settlement type="town">Cape Town</settlement></placeName></del></addrLine>
<lb/>
<addrLine><space extent="1" unit="words"/><persName>Benjamin Pyne <choice><abbr>Esqe</abbr><expan>Esquire</expan></choice></persName></addrLine>
<addrLine><space extent="3" unit="words"/><placeName>Wildingtree</placeName></addrLine>
<addrLine><space extent="5" unit="words"/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/><placeName>Ongar</placeName></addrLine>
<addrLine><space extent="5" unit="words"/><space extent="2" unit="chars"/><placeName>Essex</placeName></addrLine>
	</address></ab>

<cb rend="right vertical upside-down"/>
